  "text": "In order to avoid misinterpretation, the terms life cycle viability and life cycle affordability are defined. Life cycle viability (in urban development) is defined as merging economic and environmental sustainability [CITATION_1] . Life cycle affordability is defined as a calculated net present value measure (V/m 2 /a) representing overall costefficiency during a defined time period.",
